    public class PVWriterConfiguration<T>

      • timeout

        public PVWriterConfiguration<T> timeout(org.epics.util.time.TimeDuration timeout,
                               String timeoutMessage)
        Sets a timeout for write operations.

        When a write operation lasts longer than the given timeout, a notification is sent with a TimeoutException. Note that, in the current implementation, the write is not cancelled and may still trigger a second notification. With a synch write, the method returns at the timeout expiration with the exception.

        Parameters:
        timeout - the duration of the timeout; can't be null
        timeoutMessage - the message for the reported timeout
        Returns:
        this expression

      • writeListener

        public PVWriterConfiguration<T> writeListener(PVWriterListener<? extends T> listener)
        Adds a listener notified for any writer event (write result, connection and errors).

        Registering a listener here guarantees that no event is ever missed.

        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to register
        Returns:
        this expression
